Jacob Humphreys (Picture: Sapa) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories On Friday, the SCA reduced Jacob Humphreys's sentence to eight years' imprisonment. It set aside the murder counts, replacing them with 10 counts of culpable homicide. It also set aside four counts of attempted murder."The sentences imposed by the trial court are set aside and replaced with the following: Eight years imprisonment which is dated to 28 February 2012," the SCA, in Bloemfontein, said in papers.Humphreys overtook a queue of cars waiting at the Buttskop level-crossing, Cape Town, on 25 August 2010, and tried to cross the railway line, even though the safety booms were down. Ten children died and four were seriously injured when the train hit his minibus.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.